parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or shift erratically, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded in traffic.
symptoms: The transmission shifts hard or erratically
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the transmission overheats
the vehicle shudders or vibrates
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle accelerates suddenly or unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the transmission to fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded in traffic.
symptoms: The transmission shudders or vibrates
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the transmission overheats
the torque converter fails
the transmission slips or hesitates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch or brake system can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded in traffic.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal is difficult to depress
the vehicle hesitates or stalls when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the driveline-protection system can cause unintended braking on the wheel on the opposite side of the failed sensor, leading to the vehicle pulling to one side unexpectedly, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The brakes inflate on their own as if someone is pressing them down while driving
causing the vehicle to jerk horribly
making it difficult to steer or maintain control of the vehicle or stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The engine power is reduced
the vehicle stalls
the check engine warning light is illuminated
and the vehicle may not accelerate as normal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience a loss of control, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the check engine warning light is illuminated
the voltage at the dash drops
and the headlights may not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The radio changes channels by itself
the menus change by themselves
the instrument screen changes from info to audio by itself
and calls are made to the last number by itself.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear window defroster can cause the rear window to shatter, leading to a loss of visibility and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The rear window defroster overheats
causing the back electric sliding window to shatter.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trailer brake system can cause the vehicle to experience unintended braking, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The service trailer brake system warning light is illuminated
the audible message appears
and the vehicle may experience unintended braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vacuum pump can cause the brake pedal to become hard or spongy, leading to increased braking effort and extended stopping distances, which can increase the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the brake pedal to become hard or spongy, leading to increased braking effort and extended stopping distances, which can increase the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trailer brake system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to increased braking effort and extended stopping distances, which can increase the risk of a crash.
symptoms: "Service Trailer Brake System" warning light comes on
trailer brakes stop working
persistent chiming and warning messages
inability to hear phone calls or music
inability to see digital speedometer readout.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake assist system can cause the brake pedal to become hard or spongy, leading to increased braking effort and extended stopping distances, which can increase the risk of a crash.
symptoms: "Service Brake Assist" warning light comes on
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The squeaky/popping noise when braking can indicate a problem with the brake system, which can lead to increased braking effort and extended stopping distances, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Squeaky/popping noise when stepping on the brake pedal
noise becomes constant when braking frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become stiff or lock up, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering system fails
causing the steering wheel to become stiff or lock up
loss of power steering assist
reduced power steering
steering wheel jerking out of hands
and difficulty turning the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the loss of power steering, stability control, and other essential systems, leading to a loss of vehicle control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The electrical system fails
causing the loss of power steering
stability control
and other essential systems
resulting in a loss of vehicle control
reduced power steering
and difficulty turning the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The reduction of steering assist can cause the steering wheel to become stiff or difficult to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering assist is reduced
causing the steering wheel to become stiff or difficult to turn
making it challenging to control the vehicle
and displaying warning messages such as "steering assist reduced" or "service trailer brake".

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake system fails
causing the vehicle to lose braking ability
resulting in a loss of vehicle control
and displaying warning messages such as "service brake system".

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stability control system can cause the vehicle to lose traction and stability, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The stability control system fails
causing the vehicle to lose traction and stability
resulting in a loss of vehicle control
and displaying warning messages such as "stability control system requires servicing".
